oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Framed triptyic photographs of John William Batterham Lindsey
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Three photographs of John Williams Batterham Lindsey of Chattanooga. In all three Still Images he is wearing a junior officer's uniform with a single rank bar visible on each shoulder. He was a student at the Univ. of Tenn. and volunteered for service. He served in the 81st Division. He trained at Fort Jackson, South Carolina.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Lindsey, John William Batterham
